               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460817-name-313" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-313" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-313" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460817-name-313" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MOORE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to a coal-merchant at Phœnix-wharf, South<lb></lb>wark. On the 26th of July I was on board a steam-boat, at Old Shades-pier—I felt something touch my pocket—I turned and saw the prisoner make away to another part of the boat—I stopped him, and felt my pocket—I missed my handkerchief—I asked him to give it me, as I felt sure he had it, from the manner he was making away—he denied having it—I noticed him closing his arm to his side—I removed his arm—his trowsers pocket fell down, and I found my handkerchief in his pocket.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character, and a witness engaged to employ him.)</p>
